OL,1,D]S737{kkkc5FOver 7 million struggling  
OL,2,D]S555{jjj25Fwith bills, survey finds   
OL,3,D]Suuu{rrzq5F                           
OL,4,T#######################################
OL,5, Some 7.4 million UK adults are still   
OL,6, struggling to pay bills due to the high
OL,7, cost of living, a survey suggests.     
OL,9,FThe number has fallen from last year,  
OL,10,Faccording to the Financial Conduct     
OL,11,FAuthority (FCA), but many households   
OL,12,Fstill feel "heavily burdened".         
OL,14,FIts survey suggested one in nine adults
OL,15,F(5.5 million) had missed a bill or     
OL,16,Fcredit payment in the six months to    
OL,17,FJanuary 2024.                          
OL,19,FOne in nine people also had no         
OL,20,Fdisposable income, the FCA said.       
